SNCF have complained to French prosecutors over the 'extremely grave and irresponsible action' of the Paris-Roubaix cyclists who breached a safety barrier as a train approached . 
  The last of the riders went through the barrier eight seconds before the TGV train hurtled through . 
  One rider was even clipped by the barrier as it came down . 
  SNCF said the action risked a deadly tragedy and has complained to police . 
  John Degenkolb won the race and was among the riders who breached the barrier . 
 